LorebookItems.value:
The recreation hall is filled with board games, a pool table, and comfy seating. Colorful murals painted by past campers cover the walls. This space is perfect for indoor activities and evening programs, buzzing with laughter and friendly competition. An old jukebox in the corner often plays nostalgic tunes.
"Ethan":{"hair":"bandana_black","wears":"big_cargo_shorts","job":"program_coordinator"},
"Olivia":{"hair":"straight_black","wears":"multicolored_planner_funky_pens","job":"administrative_assistant"}

The sports field is a vibrant expanse of grass and dirt, buzzing with energy and activity. It hosts spirited games of soccer, volleyball, and frisbee. Basic but well-loved sports gear is scattered around, ready for use. A towering, hand-painted scoreboard adds to the competitive spirit, while colorful flags marking the field flutter in the breeze. In one corner, an old tire swing hangs from a sturdy oak tree, a favorite spot for campers to take a break and cheer on their friends.
"Jake":{"hair":"short_blonde","wears":"tight_athletic_gear_headband","job":"camp_counselor"},
"Jenna":{"hair":"shoulder_length_red","wears":"neon_gear_megaphone","job":"CIT_coordinator"}

Aiden (Nature Guide, Male, Wilderness Survival Enthusiast):
Aiden, the nature guide with a messy red mop of hair and a perpetually misplaced machete, talks a big game about inner peace and nature’s wisdom. He’s often caught spouting faux-philosophical nonsense while munching on trail mix. Known for his "zen" attitude that quickly dissolves under pressure. His survival skills demonstrations often involve over-the-top antics, like wrestling a "wild" (stuffed) bear or building a shelter out of toothpicks and duct tape. His storytelling sessions are filled with exaggerated tales of near-death experiences and mythical creatures, leaving campers both terrified and entertained. Aiden often speaks in a fake, Australian accent, owing to his idolization of Steve Irwin.
"Aiden":{"hair":"messy_red","wears":"outdoor_gear_machete","job":"nature_guide", "fake Buddhist"}

Jake (Camp Counselor, Male, Former College Athlete):
Jake is the overly enthusiastic Camp Counselor with the build of a superhero and the energy of a caffeinated squirrel. Always seen in his ridiculously tight athletic gear and a headband, he treats every activity like an Olympic event. Known for his absurd motivational speeches that often end in inexplicable pyrotechnics, Jake can turn a simple game of tug-of-war into a full-blown action movie sequence. His hidden talent is playing the guitar, which he does while performing backflips and shouting out extreme sports clichés.
"Jake":{"hair":"short_blonde","wears":"tight_athletic_gear_headband","job":"camp_counselor", "macho wannabe"}

Mia (Arts and Crafts Director, Female, Environmental Science Major):
Mia, the artsy and slightly paranoid director of arts and crafts, is always dressed in tie-dye and patchwork clothing. She’s convinced that someone is out to sabotage her craft projects, often hiding her supplies in the most unexpected places. Despite her quirks, her creativity knows no bounds, and she can turn a pile of junk into a masterpiece. She once built an entire sculpture out of recycled soda cans, convinced they were being stolen when no one was looking. Her nature walks are legendary, mainly because they include impromptu tree-hugging sessions and dramatic readings of poetry to squirrels.
"Mia":{"hair":"long_wavy_brown","wears":"tie_dye_patchwork_clothing","job":"arts_and_crafts_director", "paranoid"}

Leo (Head Chef, Male, Culinary School Graduate):
Leo is the camp’s well-meaning but airheaded head chef. Always seen in his towering toque and chef's coat, he’s known for his culinary experiments that range from genius to utterly bizarre. He’s got a habit of forgetting key ingredients and often wanders off mid-recipe. Once, he tried to make spaghetti with marshmallows, much to the campers' confusion and delight. He’s famous for his impromptu cooking shows, complete with a live studio audience (the campers) and his signature move: flambéing everything in sight.
"Leo":{"hair":"short_black","wears":"chef_coat_tall_toque","job":"head_chef", "airhead"}

Sophie (Lifeguard, Female, Marine Biology Student):
Sophie is the lifeguard with a penchant for tall tales. Her brown hair always in a ponytail and mirrored sunglasses perpetually perched on her nose, she patrols the lake with a confident swagger. Known for her exaggerated stories about saving lives and wrestling alligators, she keeps campers entertained and skeptical. She once claimed to have single-handedly fended off a shark with nothing but a pool noodle. She loves sharing bizarre marine facts, like the mating habits of sea cucumbers, during swim breaks, often leading to hilariously confused campers.
"Sophie":{"hair":"ponytail_brown","wears":"red_lifeguard_suit_mirrored_sunglasses","job":"lifeguard", "liar"}

Grace (Camp Director, Female, Experienced Camp Leader):
Grace runs Camp Cookamunga with the intensity of a drill sergeant and the charisma of a DMV clerk. She is openly dismissive of campers and completely unhelpful. Her silver-streaked hair is always in a no-nonsense bun, and she wields her clipboard like a weapon. Known for her strict, no-nonsense approach, she has a knack for making campers and staff alike avoid her if at all possible. Though unsubstantiated, rumor has it, she once killed a bear with her bare hands and ate its liver.
"Grace":{"hair":"silver_streaked","wears":"military_style_bun_clipboard","job":"camp_director","mean"}

Mark (Assistant to the Camp Director, Male, Outdoor Education Specialist):
Mark is the ultimate brown-noser, always ready to jump in with an enthusiastic "Yes, Grace!" His collection of quirky T-shirts, featuring everything from anime women to bad puns, contrasts sharply with his overly eager demeanor. Despite being a major suck-up, he's strangely endearing and somehow manages to get things done, even if he trips over himself doing it.
"Mark":{"hair":"short_brown","wears":"cargo_shorts_quirky_t_shirts","job":"assistant_camp_director","suck-up"}

Linda (Camp Nurse, Female, Health Officer):
Linda is the camp's resident mom, always ready with a band-aid, a cookie, and a hug. Her cartoon-themed scrubs and ever-present first aid kit make her a comforting sight. She has a knack for turning even the most minor scrape into a dramatic rescue mission, complete with cookies for the "brave patient." She's so nurturing, some campers fake injuries just to get her attention. She’s also known for her hilariously melodramatic diagnoses, declaring sprained ankles as “catastrophic leg implosions.”
"Linda":{"hair":"short_blonde","wears":"cartoon_scrubs_first_aid_kit","job":"health_officer", "mommy"}

Ethan (Program Coordinator, Male, Recreational Therapy Major):
Ethan is the goofball of Camp Cookamunga, always in his signature bandana and, inexplicably, speedos, regardless of the weather. He’s the master of fun and chaos, turning every activity into an over-the-top spectacle. Known for his slapstick humor and wild antics, he once convinced the entire camp to join a synchronized swimming routine in the mess hall.
"Ethan":{"hair":"bandana_black","wears":"speedos","job":"program_coordinator", "goofball"}

Olivia (Administrative Assistant, Female, Business Management Student):
Olivia is the jittery, hyper-organized administrative assistant, always clutching her multicolored planner and a rainbow of funky pens. She’s perpetually on edge, jumping at every loud noise and often losing her glasses in the most ridiculous places. Despite her jumpiness, she somehow keeps the camp running smoothly, even if she sometimes screams at the sight of a harmless spider. She has a penchant for organizing hilariously themed days, such as “Dress Like a Superhero Monday” and “Talk Like a Pirate Tuesday,” complete with over-the-top props and costumes.
"Olivia":{"hair":"straight_black","wears":"multicolored_planner_funky_pens","job":"administrative_assistant", "jumpy"}

Tom (Maintenance Supervisor, Male, Skilled Handyman):
Tom is the laid-back, easygoing maintenance guy who seems to be in a constant state of chill. His curly hair peeks out from under a battered trucker hat, and his tool belt is always slung low around his waist. Known for his leisurely pace and tendency to "take breaks" in the woods, Tom can fix anything – if you give him enough time and snacks. He once spent an entire day trying to fix a light bulb because he got distracted by the "pretty colors." He’s famous for his disastrous yet delicious campfire cooking, often involving ingredients like marshmallow fluff and cans of hairspray, and his tall tales of handyman escapades that invariably end in exaggerated, Looney Tunes-style mishaps.
"Tom":{"hair":"curly_brown","wears":"tool_belt_trucker_hat","job":"maintenance_supervisor", "stoner"}

Jenna (CIT Coordinator, Female, Education Major):
Jenna is the spirited CIT (Counselors in Training) Coordinator, who can often be found in neon gear, clutching a megaphone with a determination that borders on delusional. A drama and band girl at heart, Jenna always dreamed of being a cheerleader, despite her lack of coordination and the typical cheerleader physique. Her cheer routines are a chaotic mix of Broadway flair and band camp precision, often ending in unplanned pratfalls and accidental musical numbers. She’s known for her spontaneous dance-offs and her hilariously catchy camp-themed songs, which often include choreographed routines and an absurd number of jazz hands.
"Jenna":{"hair":"shoulder_length_red","wears":"neon_gear_megaphone","job":"CIT_coordinator", "nerd"}

